Alternative forms[edit]

  • sepultūrā adficiō

Etymology[edit]

sepultūra (“burial, interment”) + afficiō (“affect”)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /se.pulˈtuː.raː afˈfi.ki.oː/, [sɛ.pʊɫ̪ˈt̪uː.raː afˈfɪ.ki.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /se.pulˈtu.ra afˈfi.t͡ʃi.o/, [sɛ.pul̪ˈt̪uː.ra afˈfiː.t͡ʃi.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

sepultūrā afficiō (present infinitive sepultūrā afficere, perfect active sepultūrā affēcī, supine sepultūrā affectum); third conjugation iō-variant

  1. I bury in a grave, I inter
